ected elements at positions `p_k` and `p_{k+1}`, the number of removed elements between them is `(p_{k+1} - p_k - 1)`, so `d_{p_{k+1}} = d_{p_k} + (p_{k+1} - p_k - 1)`. This means `d` values must be non-decreasing, and specifically `d_{k+1} - d_k = p_{k+1} - p_k - 1 >= 0`, which is automatically satisfied.\n\nSo the problem reduces to: longest non-decreasing subsequence of `d` values (in original order) among elements where `d >= 0`.\n\nThe code computes this, but it **sorts elements by `(v, -d)`** instead of processing them in original order. This is wrong.\n\nThe longest non-decreasing subsequence should be computed on the `d` values **in original positional order**, not sorted by value.\n\n{\"verdict\": \"FAIL\", \"bugs\": [{\"description\": \"Elements are sorted by (v, -d) instead of being processed in their original order (by position). The longest non-decreasing subsequence of d values must respect the original ordering of elements in the sequence.\", \"line\": 14, \"severity\": \"critical\", \"triggering_input\": \"4\\n4 2 3 1\"}]}",
